{
  "text": "In this section, a comparison between the classic DM and ICPQR-based DM is presented. Figure 4 .4 shows the two-dimensional DM embedding of X , and a two-dimensional view of an aligned versions of ICPQR-based DM, applied to X with three different distortion values. It should be stressed that h [CITATION_1] s , which is the output of Algorithm 4, is an s-dimensional 2\u00b5-distortion of the n-dimensional DM \u03a8 [CITATION_2] as defined in Definition 1.1. Therefore, it is unlikely that low-dimensional projections (lower than s) will represent similar geometries. Nevertheless, to demonstrate the notion of low-rate distortion, Fig. 4 .4 shows a two dimensional view of an aligned version of \u03a8 [CITATION_3] with \u03a8 [CITATION_4] . For that purpose, the DM of X was explicitly computed. The utilized alignment algorithm is described in Appendix A.",
